7 permanent and expanded to all courts; and
8 8. Recommendations for statutory changes which may be needed if the
9 program is to be made permanent and expanded to all courts.
10 (4) The Administrative Office of the Courts:
11 (a) Shall provide an annual report to the Legislative Research Commission for
12 referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Judiciary by September 1 of each
13 year the program is in operation with statistics, findings, and
14 recommendations; and
15 (b) May make periodic progress reports and statistical reports and provide
16 suggestions to the Legislative Research Commission when determined
17 necessary by the Chief Justice.
